    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Go to Settings - Privacy & Security - Security - HTTPS-only mode and disable it.\r\n2. Exit the Settings pages, and type http://permission.site in the search bar (or http://badssl.com).\r\n3. Observe the URL after the page is loaded.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe page loads as http page, exactly how the user typed it.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThe page loads as https, regardless of how the user typed the URL.\r\nOnly if the parameter `dom.security.https_first_pbm` is changed in about:config to `false`, the HTTPS-Only mode option works properly.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: all\r\n* Focus version: Focus Nightly 104.0a1 from 7/19, and Beta 103.0.0-beta.5\r\n* In Fenix Nightly normal browsing the HTTPS only mode works\r\n* In the short video below is the behavior if the pref in the about:config isn't modified:\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/179674275-a0ad98e8-f930-443b-a5b5-4aead6f984e8.mp4\r\n\r\n* In the short video below is the behavior when the user modifies the `dom.security.https_first_pbm` in about:config to `false`\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/179674378-aaccd973-c10f-4547-a1bd-af8d518ab36a.mp4\r\n\r\n",
